</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9036959C5A7409FF58FF073576FDDF" blockId="10.[151,1436,222,1182]" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">
This is another very diverse genus, comprising probably not less than 
<number id="3DE724B29C5A7409FC62FF0733EFFF3F" box="[941,969,222,246]" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" value="24.0">24</number>
species in Grande Terre. Several of them (all undescribed) were collected from various species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D169C5A7409FCE0FEDA3355FED2" box="[815,883,259,283]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cunoniaceae" genus="Codia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Oxalidales" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95BEA879C5A7409FCE0FEDA3355FED2" box="[815,883,259,283]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">Codia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D169C5A7409FC49FEDB3438FED3" box="[902,1054,258,282]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cunoniaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Oxalidales" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Cunoniaceae</taxonomicName>
). Adults of one species (over 
<specimenCount id="9D29FD1C9C5A7409FA4FFEDB312AFEF7" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" type="generic">
<number id="3DE724B29C5A7409FA4FFEDB35BAFED3" box="[1408,1436,258,282]" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" value="40.0">40</number>
specimens
</specimenCount>
collected) were observed feeding on young leaves of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D169C5A7409FCA3FEFF3432FEF7" box="[876,1044,294,318]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cunoniaceae" genus="Codia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Oxalidales" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="discolor">
<emphasis id="B95BEA879C5A7409FCA3FEFF3432FEF7" box="[876,1044,294,318]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">Codia discolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
several times (
<figureCitation id="13142A109C5A7409FB71FEFF356EFEF7" box="[1214,1352,294,318]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 20. 15" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1845,1868]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,287,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,287,1832]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 20. 15) Pterapion kanalae feeding on fresh leaf of Pycnandra balansae; 16) Aprotapion hamiota feeding on Codia incrassata; 16) feeding holes of Tetrapion n. sbgen. et sp. on C. incrassata; 17) adult of Tetrapion n. sbgen. et sp. feeding on inflorescence of C. incrassata; 18, 19) feeding holes of Tetrapion (s. str.) sp. on fresh stems and leaves of C. discolor. (phot.: all—MW; sites: 15 — Aoupinié, 16 — ca. 1 km NW Mt Mandjélia, 17, 18 — Mt Mandjélia, 19, 20 — Bois du Sud)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282870/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">Figs. 19, 20</figureCitation>
). Other plants associated with the weevils are 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D169C5A7409FD82FE9232E6FEAA" box="[589,704,331,355]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cunoniaceae" genus="Codia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Oxalidales" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jaffreyi">
<emphasis id="B95BEA879C5A7409FD82FE923246FEAB" box="[589,608,331,354]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B95BEA879C5A7409FDBFFE9232E6FEAA" box="[624,704,331,355]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">jaffreyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D169C5A7409FD00FE923315FEAA" box="[719,819,331,355]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cunoniaceae" genus="Codia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Oxalidales" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nitida">
<emphasis id="B95BEA879C5A7409FD00FE9232C4FEAB" box="[719,738,331,354]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B95BEA879C5A7409FD3DFE923315FEAA" box="[754,819,331,355]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">nitida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and (in the North of Grande Terre) 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D169C5A7409FB16FE923556FEAA" box="[1241,1392,331,355]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cunoniaceae" genus="Codia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Oxalidales" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="incrassata">
<emphasis id="B95BEA879C5A7409FB16FE9234CAFEAB" box="[1241,1260,331,354]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B95BEA879C5A7409FB33FE953556FEAA" box="[1276,1392,332,355]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">incrassata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, on which at least two members of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D169C5A7409FE39FEB63244FE4F" box="[502,610,367,390]" class="Insecta" family="Coleoptera" genus="Tetrapion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="B95BEA879C5A7409FE39FEB63244FE4F" box="[502,610,367,390]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">Tetrapion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26857FC9C5A7409FDA5FEB63283FE4F" box="[618,677,367,390]" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
have regularly been observed, apart from another, wingless species representing a new subgenus (see below). Seven specimens of one species were collected at night from one plant of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D169C5A7409FF58FE6F31B4FE07" box="[151,402,438,462]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cunoniaceae" genus="Pancheria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Oxalidales" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="billardierii">
<emphasis id="B95BEA879C5A7409FF58FE6F31B4FE07" box="[151,402,438,462]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">Pancheria billardierii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, another 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D169C5A7409FDCAFE6F32B0FE07" box="[517,662,438,462]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cunoniaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Oxalidales" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Cunoniaceae</taxonomicName>
[
<number id="3DE724B29C5A7409FD65FE6F32EAFE07" box="[682,716,438,462]" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" value="22.0">22</number>
]. In some northern and central localities (Thoven, Aoupinié, Mandjélia, Farino) 
<number id="3DE724B29C5A7409FEB8FE033187FE3B" box="[375,417,474,498]" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
undescribed species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D169C5A7409FD73FE05330EFE3A" box="[700,808,476,499]" class="Insecta" family="Coleoptera" genus="Tetrapion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95BEA879C5A7409FD73FE05330EFE3A" box="[700,808,476,499]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">Tetrapion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of one distinct species-group were repeatedly beaten, often in numbers, from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D169C5A7409FE6FFE263251FDDF" box="[416,631,510,534]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Guioa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="microsepala">
<emphasis id="B95BEA879C5A7409FE6FFE263251FDDF" box="[416,631,510,534]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">Guioa microsepala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D169C5A7409FD4BFE2632C0FDDF" box="[644,742,510,534]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Guioa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ovalis">
<emphasis id="B95BEA879C5A7409FD4BFE2632B3FDDF" box="[644,661,511,534]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B95BEA879C5A7409FD6CFE2732C0FDDF" box="[675,742,510,534]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">ovalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D169C5A7409FD3BFE263379FDDF" box="[756,863,510,534]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Guioa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glauca">
<emphasis id="B95BEA879C5A7409FD3BFE263323FDDF" box="[756,773,511,534]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B95BEA879C5A7409FCDCFE273379FDDF" box="[787,863,510,534]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">glauca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D169C5A7409FC53FE26340EFDDF" box="[924,1064,511,534]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Cupaniopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95BEA879C5A7409FC53FE26340EFDDF" box="[924,1064,511,534]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">Cupaniopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (all 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D169C5A7409FB7BFE273563FDDF" box="[1204,1349,510,534]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Sapindaceae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9036959C5A7409FF08FDFA34F4FD03" blockId="10.[151,1436,222,1182]" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">
Most members of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D169C5A7409FE6CFDFD3229FDF2" box="[419,527,548,571]" class="Insecta" family="Coleoptera" genus="Tetrapion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95BEA879C5A7409FE6CFDFD3229FDF2" box="[419,527,548,571]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">Tetrapion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have short, thick, and sexually not differentiated rostra, allowing for a very shallow deposition of eggs, presumably subcortical or directly into soft, green tissues. Such a shape for the female rostrum generally excludes larval development in reproductive organs of the plant, and indeed, the beetles have never been observed on flowers or fruits. However, several poorly known, tiny species of this diverse genus have females with long, thin and curved rostra specialized for preparation of deeper oviposition holes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9036959C5A7409FF08FD0F34BCFCFF" blockId="10.[151,1436,222,1182]" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">
Although recently collected several times in Grande Terre and Loyalty Is (Lifou), nothing can be concluded about plant preferences of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D169C5A7409FE1CFD253361FCDB" authority="Wanat, 2001" authorityName="Wanat" authorityYear="2001" box="[467,839,762,787]" class="Insecta" family="Coleoptera" genus="Tetrapion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thoracicum" subGenus="Axinapion">
<emphasis id="B95BEA879C5A7409FE1CFD2531C6FCDA" box="[467,480,764,787]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">T</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis id="B95BEA879C5A7409FE33FD22322BFCDA" box="[508,525,763,787]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">A</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="B95BEA879C5A7409FDE6FD22328FFCDA" box="[553,681,763,787]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">thoracicum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBE4B649C5A7409FD7BFD223361FCDB" author="Wanat" box="[692,839,762,786]" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" refString="Wanat, M. (2001) Genera of Australo-Pacific Rhadinocybinae and Myrmacicelinae, with biogeography of the Apionidae (Coleoptera: Curculionoidea) and phylogeny of the Brentidae (s. lato). Mantis, Olsztyn, 432 pp." type="book" year="2001">
Wanat, 
<number id="3DE724B29C5A7409FCC3FD233361FCDB" box="[780,839,762,786]" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" value="2001.0">2001</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, the sole member of the subgenus 
<emphasis id="B95BEA879C5A7409FB27FD223545FCDA" box="[1256,1379,763,787]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">Axinapion.</emphasis>
One specimen was incidentally beaten from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D169C5A7409FD9CFCC7331FFCFF" box="[595,825,798,822]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapotaceae" genus="Pycnandra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="balansae">
<emphasis id="B95BEA879C5A7409FD9CFCC7331FFCFF" box="[595,825,798,822]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">Pycnandra balansae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D169C5A7409FC87FCC733EFFCFF" box="[840,969,798,822]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapotaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Sapotaceae</taxonomicName>
) in Aoupinié [
<number id="3DE724B29C5A7409FBA3FCC734A8FCFF" box="[1132,1166,798,822]" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" value="23.0">23</number>
].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9036959C5A7409FF08FC9A3175FB57" blockId="10.[151,1436,222,1182]" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">
A peculiar flightless species was discovered on Mt Mandjélia by Mrs L. E. Cheesmann nearly 
<number id="3DE724B29C5A7409FB20FC9B352DFC93" box="[1263,1291,834,858]" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" value="60.0">60</number>
years ago (
<number id="3DE724B29C5A7409FA5FFC9B35BAFC93" box="[1424,1436,834,858]" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" value="1.0">1</number>
<number id="3DE724B29C5A7409FF58FCBE308AFCB6" box="[151,172,871,895]" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" value="3.0">3</number>
, Natural History Museum, London), and provisionally placed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D169C5A7409FC48FCBE34A9FCB7" authority="Apterapion" authorityName="Apterapion" box="[903,1167,870,894]" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Pterapion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95BEA879C5A7409FC48FCBE33D1FCB7" box="[903,1015,871,894]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">Pterapion</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B95BEA879C5A7409FBC7FCBF34A0FCB7" box="[1032,1158,870,894]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">Apterapion</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBE4B649C5A7409FB75FCBE3570FCB7" author="Wanat" box="[1210,1366,870,894]" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" refString="Wanat, M. (2001) Genera of Australo-Pacific Rhadinocybinae and Myrmacicelinae, with biogeography of the Apionidae (Coleoptera: Curculionoidea) and phylogeny of the Brentidae (s. lato). Mantis, Olsztyn, 432 pp." type="book" year="2001">
Wanat (
<number id="3DE724B29C5A7409FADFFCBF356BFCB7" box="[1296,1357,870,894]" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" value="2001.0">2001</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. After a re-discovery of this species on the summit of Mt Mandjélia by MW in 
<number id="3DE724B29C5A7409FC0DFC5333DBFC6B" box="[962,1021,906,930]" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" value="2007.0">2007</number>
, and thorough morphological studies of several dozen specimens of both sexes, the species is now considered to represent a new subgenus within 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D169C5A7409FF58FC0D3127FC22" box="[151,257,980,1003]" class="Insecta" family="Coleoptera" genus="Tetrapion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95BEA879C5A7409FF58FC0D3127FC22" box="[151,257,980,1003]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">Tetrapion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, not a congener of 
<emphasis id="B95BEA879C5A7409FE11FC0A32E6FC22" box="[478,704,979,1003]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">
Apterapion 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D169C5A7409FDABFC0A32E6FC22" box="[612,704,979,1003]" class="Insecta" family="Brentidae" genus="Aprotapion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamiota">hamiota</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
. It is noteworthy that both these species were found on the same host and plant community, but allopatric on two hills separated by less than 
<quantity id="4CD79B709C5A7409FB8BFC2F34AEFBC7" box="[1092,1160,1014,1038]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" unit="km" value="1.0">1 km</quantity>
. The new 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D169C5A7409FAC0FC2E355EFBC7" box="[1295,1400,1015,1038]" class="Insecta" family="Coleoptera" genus="Tetrapion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95BEA879C5A7409FAC0FC2E355EFBC7" box="[1295,1400,1015,1038]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">Tetrapion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is monophagous on 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D169C5A7409FEA9FBC2320CFBFA" box="[358,554,1051,1075]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cunoniaceae" genus="Codia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Oxalidales" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="incrassata">
<emphasis id="B95BEA879C5A7409FEA9FBC2320CFBFA" box="[358,554,1051,1075]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">Codia incrassata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D169C5A7409FDF3FBC332F5FBFB" box="[572,723,1050,1074]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cunoniaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Oxalidales" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Cunoniaceae</taxonomicName>
), and beetles feed both on inflorescences (
<figureCitation id="13142A109C5A7409FB07FBC3353BFBFB" box="[1224,1309,1050,1074]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 20. 15" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1845,1868]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,287,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,287,1832]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 20. 15) Pterapion kanalae feeding on fresh leaf of Pycnandra balansae; 16) Aprotapion hamiota feeding on Codia incrassata; 16) feeding holes of Tetrapion n. sbgen. et sp. on C. incrassata; 17) adult of Tetrapion n. sbgen. et sp. feeding on inflorescence of C. incrassata; 18, 19) feeding holes of Tetrapion (s. str.) sp. on fresh stems and leaves of C. discolor. (phot.: all—MW; sites: 15 — Aoupinié, 16 — ca. 1 km NW Mt Mandjélia, 17, 18 — Mt Mandjélia, 19, 20 — Bois du Sud)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282870/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">
Fig. 
<number id="3DE724B29C5A7409FACFFBC3353BFBFB" box="[1280,1309,1050,1074]" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
) and fresh leaves (
<figureCitation id="13142A109C5A7409FF24FBE73118FB9F" box="[235,318,1086,1110]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 20. 15" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1845,1868]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,287,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,287,1832]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 20. 15) Pterapion kanalae feeding on fresh leaf of Pycnandra balansae; 16) Aprotapion hamiota feeding on Codia incrassata; 16) feeding holes of Tetrapion n. sbgen. et sp. on C. incrassata; 17) adult of Tetrapion n. sbgen. et sp. feeding on inflorescence of C. incrassata; 18, 19) feeding holes of Tetrapion (s. str.) sp. on fresh stems and leaves of C. discolor. (phot.: all—MW; sites: 15 — Aoupinié, 16 — ca. 1 km NW Mt Mandjélia, 17, 18 — Mt Mandjélia, 19, 20 — Bois du Sud)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282870/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">
Fig. 
<number id="3DE724B29C5A7409FED0FBE73118FB9F" box="[287,318,1086,1110]" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
). Nevertheless, no hypothesis can be formulated about the way of larval development of this species after negative results from 
<emphasis id="B95BEA879C5A7409FE0BFBBD322FFBB2" box="[452,521,1124,1147]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">in situ</emphasis>
controls of flower heads and fresh leaf buds of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D169C5A7409FBD1FBBA3495FBB2" box="[1054,1203,1123,1147]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cunoniaceae" genus="Codia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Oxalidales" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="incrassata">
<emphasis id="B95BEA879C5A7409FBD1FBBA3417FBB3" box="[1054,1073,1123,1146]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B95BEA879C5A7409FBF1FBBD3495FBB2" box="[1086,1203,1124,1147]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="69">incrassata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<date id="FF9110559C5A7409FB19FBBA354AFBB3" box="[1238,1388,1122,1147]" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" value="2007-01">
January 
<number id="3DE724B29C5A7409FAFBFBBB354AFBB3" box="[1332,1388,1122,1146]" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</date>
and 
<date id="FF9110559C5A7409FF58FB5F3176FB57" box="[151,336,1158,1182]" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" value="2008-11">
November 
<number id="3DE724B29C5A7409FEDBFB5F3176FB57" box="[276,336,1158,1182]" pageId="10" pageNumber="69" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</date>
.
